%N A395794 Decimal expansion of the moment of inertia of an oloid with unit mass density, formed by two unit circles, about an axis through the center of mass perpendicular to the line connecting the centers of the circles.
%C A395794 By choosing axes such that the origin is the midpoint of the line segment connecting the centers of the two circles and the x-axis passes through these centers, the moment of inertia tensor is diagonal. In this coordinate system, I_{xx} = A395793, and I_{yy} = I_{zz} both equal to this constant.
%H A395794 Robert Ferréol, <a href="https://www.mathcurve.com/surfaces.gb/orthobicycle/orthobicycle.shtml">Oloid</a>, MathCurve.
%H A395794 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.15145">The moment of inertia tensor of an oloid</a>, arXiv:2603.15145 [math.MG], 2026.
%H A395794 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CompleteEllipticIntegraloftheFirstKind.html">Complete Elliptic Integral of the First Kind</a>.
